    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-06T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-06T05:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">560.AL/10–647: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Troutman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">us urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-06T11:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 6, 1947—11 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1084. Personal for Wilcox from Brown. Have reached satisfactory agreement Coombs.
                        <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> acts today:<note n="1" xml:id="d511fn1"
                        >In telegram 1088 from Geneva, October 6, not printed, Brown reported that
                        the Trade Agreements Committee “unanimously approved agreement I reached
                        with Coombs.” (560.AL/10–647)</note> Australian Cabinet acts tomorrow.
                        <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> yesterday tentatively agreed recommend
                    agreement UK general basis outlined <gloss target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss>
                    1077, October 4.<note n="2" xml:id="d511fn2">Not printed.</note> Final decision
                    today. Am well satisfied.</p>
                <p>Having serious difficulty Canada apple preference. Seeing Wilgress again today.
                    [Brown.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Troutman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
